    </editorialNote><section id="ID_1438403394055_001" name="s6" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-04-23" status="operational" temporalId="s6"><num value="6">6.</num><heading>Effect of this Ordinance</heading><leadIn>Any act done under—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438413120449_005" name="a" temporalId="s6_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>the Hong Kong Bill of Rights (Amendment) Ordinance 1997 (<ref href="/hk/1997/107">107 of 1997</ref>);</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413120449_013" name="b" temporalId="s6_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>the Trade Unions (Amendment) (No. 2) Ordinance 1997 (<ref href="/hk/1997/102">102 of 1997</ref>);</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413120449_021" name="c" temporalId="s6_c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content>the Employee’s Rights to Representation, Consultation and Collective Bargaining
                Ordinance
                    (<ref href="/hk/cap530">Cap.
                    530</ref>)<sup>#</sup>;
                or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438413120449_029" name="d" temporalId="s6_d"><num value="d">(d)</num><content>the Employment (Amendment) (No. 4) Ordinance 1997 (<ref href="/hk/1997/98">98
                    of 1997</ref>),</content></paragraph><continued>shall remain valid to the extent that it was valid immediately prior to the
            commencement*
            of this Ordinance as if this Ordinance had not been enacted.</continued></section><editorialNote type="footnote" id="ID_1585125623032_001" class="font_size_9">
